The performance issue is caused by the use of `zipWithIndex` in hot paths, which leads to unnecessary tuple allocations for each element in the collection being iterated. To improve performance, I will replace these `zipWithIndex` calls with `while` loops that use a manual index counter. This change avoids the overhead of tuple creation and garbage collection, resulting in more efficient code.

